25/01/2011
MOSCOW, Russia -- A Bulgarian national was among those killed by a suicide bomber at Moscow's Domodedovo airport on Monday (January 24th), the foreign ministry in Sofia confirmed on Tuesday. Nikolai Ivanov Ivanov, who also holds an Austrian passport, was identified among the victims based on his documents. A Serbian citizen, Milorad Miljkovic, is in hospital with injuries described as non-life threatening. In all, 35 people were killed and well over 100 were injured. The blast occurred in the international arrivals section of the airport, where people were waiting for friends and relatives. Many in Russia suspect the terror attack was the work of militants from the North Caucasus. (Darik, BNR, bTV, RIA Novosti, B92 - 25/01/11)
